<comment datatype='string'>The &lt;i&gt;otsA&lt;/i&gt; promoter is an internal weak promoter, and it is within the &lt;i&gt;otsB&lt;/i&gt; gene  and 39 nt upstream from the &lt;i&gt;otsA&lt;/i&gt; start codon. Upstream of &lt;i&gt;otsB&lt;/i&gt; there is an inverted repeat, and a half-site of this repeat is also found in front of &lt;i&gt;otsA&lt;/i&gt;. These may represent binding sites for a regulatory protein. The transcription of the &lt;i&gt;otsBA&lt;/i&gt; operon is reduced when the &lt;i&gt;rpoS&lt;/i&gt; gene is inactivated, but whether there is a &amp;sigma;&lt;sup&gt;S&lt;/sup&gt;-type interaction (direct or indirect) with the &lt;i&gt;otsBA&lt;/i&gt; operon is not known.</comment>
